@node prawa "Copyrights and distribution"

   TKSearch is a @{FG highlight}freeware@{FG text}. You don't ought to pay for it, but don't  forget,
that You use it on Your own risc.

@endnode
@node "intro" "Introduction"

   TKSearch replace one function  of  system  program  colled  search.  Both
version PPC and 68K are faster then search.

@endnode
@node "Installation" "Installation"

   Copy one of version (PPC or 68k) to your  command  directory  and  rename
on TKSearch.

@endnode
@node "req" "Requirements"

I tested it only on os 3.0

PPC version require PowerUP system.

@endnode
@node "Usage" "Usage"

To run program You ought to type:

   TKSearch FILE/S PATTERN/S

@{FG highlight}TKSearch@{FG text} - program name.

@{FG highlight}FILE@{FG text} - file (or files) to search (You can use '#?').
        This version can looking for only in one directory (without subdirectory).

@{FG highlight}PATTERN@{FG text} - string which You looking for.


@endnode
